@@ NOTES @@

Security:
  - lua_osi_db_get uses pfn_InternalQuery ONLY (read path).
  - pfn_InternalCall (write/call path) is intentionally absent from lua_osi_db_get.
  - No Delete() method is registered on the accessor table.
  - Row cap = 10,000 prevents runaway loops.

Dependencies:
  - Requires: osi_func_get_info(), osi_func_lookup_id(), alloc_args(), free_args(),
    set_arg_string(), set_arg_int(), set_arg_real(), osi_value_to_lua(),
    encode_function_handle(), pfn_InternalQuery, OSI_TYPE_GUIDSTRING.
  - All of the above are already available in main.c scope.

Testing:
  After applying this patch and rebuilding, test in the BG3SE console:
    local db = Osi.DB_Players
    local rows = db:Get()
    Ext.Print("DB_Players rows: " .. #rows)
    -- With filter:
    local filtered = Osi.DB_Players:Get("some-guid-here")
    Ext.Print("Filtered: " .. #filtered)

Known limitations in v1:
  - Multi-row enumeration via repeated pfn_InternalQuery calls is speculative.
    Osiris DB semantics may require a cursor-style API; if so, only the first
    row will be returned correctly. Runtime testing required to validate.
  - arity=0 (unknown) DBs get a 1-slot query; full arity requires the DB to
    be in g_knownFunctions or discovered via osi_func_get_info.
